2438 qboolean BG_AkimboFireSequence(int weapon, int akimboClip, int mainClip)
2439 {
2440  if (!(GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->attributes & WEAPON_ATTRIBUT_AKIMBO))
2441  {
2442  return qfalse;
2443  }
2444 
2445  if (!akimboClip)
2446  {
2447  return qfalse;
2448  }
2449 
2450  // no ammo in main weapon, must be akimbo turn
2451  if (!mainClip)
2452  {
2453  return qtrue;
2454  }
2455 
2456  // at this point, both have ammo
2457 
2458  // now check 'cycle' // (removed old method 11/5/2001)
2459  if ((akimboClip + mainClip) & 1)
2460  {
2461  return qfalse;
2462  }
2463 
2464  return qtrue;
2465 }

2525 qboolean BG_PlayerTouchesItem(playerState_t *ps, entityState_t *item, int atTime)
2526 {
2527  vec3_t origin;
2528 
2529  BG_EvaluateTrajectory(&item->pos, atTime, origin, qfalse, item->effect2Time);
2530 
2531  // we are ignoring ducked differences here
2532  if (ps->origin[0] - origin[0] > 36
2533  || ps->origin[0] - origin[0] < -36
2534  || ps->origin[1] - origin[1] > 36
2535  || ps->origin[1] - origin[1] < -36
2536  || ps->origin[2] - origin[2] > 36
2537  || ps->origin[2] - origin[2] < -36)
2538  {
2539  return qfalse;
2540  }
2541 
2542  return qtrue;
2543 }

2556 qboolean BG_AddMagicAmmo(playerState_t *ps, int *skill, team_t teamNum, int numOfClips)
2557 {
2558  qboolean ammoAdded = qfalse;
2559  weapon_t weapon;
2560 
2561  for (weapon = WP_NONE; weapon < WP_NUM_WEAPONS; weapon++)
2562  {
2563  if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->useAmmo)
2564  {
2565  int maxAmmo;
2566  weapon_t clip;
2567 
2568 #ifdef GAMEDLL
2569  if (team_riflegrenades.integer == 0)
2570  {
2571  switch (weapon)
2572  {
2573  case WP_GPG40:
2574  case WP_M7:
2575  continue;
2576  default:
2577  break;
2578  }
2579  }
2580 #endif
2581 
2582  // special case for grenades, they must be linked to the correct team
2583  // and they may don't appear in weapons bit-wise (see PM_SwitchIfEmpty and Add_Ammo)
2584  if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->type & WEAPON_TYPE_GRENADE)
2585  {
2586  if (weapon != GetPlayerClassesData(teamNum, ps->stats[STAT_PLAYER_CLASS])->classGrenadeWeapon.weapon)
2587  {
2588  continue;
2589  }
2590 
2591  // add grenade only if we ask for
2592  if (numOfClips)
2593  {
2594  COM_BitSet(ps->weapons, weapon);
2595  }
2596  }
2597  else if (!COM_BitCheck(ps->weapons, weapon))
2598  {
2599  continue;
2600  }
2601 
2602  maxAmmo = BG_MaxAmmoForWeapon(weapon, skill, ps->stats[STAT_PLAYER_CLASS]);
2603  clip = GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->ammoIndex;;
2604 
2605  // count less the current ammo used in weapon for non-clip weapon
2606  if (!GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->useClip)
2607  {
2608  maxAmmo -= ps->ammoclip[clip];
2609  }
2610 
2611  if (ps->ammo[clip] < maxAmmo)
2612  {
2613  int weapNumOfClips;
2614 
2615  // early out
2616  if (!numOfClips)
2617  {
2618  return qtrue;
2619  }
2620  ammoAdded = qtrue;
2621

2743 void BG_CalculateSpline_r(splinePath_t *spline, vec3_t out1, vec3_t out2, float tension)
2744 {
2745  vec3_t points[18];
2746  int i;
2747  int count = spline->numControls + 2;
2748  vec3_t dist;
2749 
2750  VectorCopy(spline->point.origin, points[0]);
2751  for (i = 0; i < spline->numControls; i++)
2752  {
2753  VectorCopy(spline->controls[i].origin, points[i + 1]);
2754  }
2755  if (!spline->next)
2756  {
2757  return;
2758  //Com_Error( ERR_DROP, "Spline (%s) with no target referenced", spline->point.name );
2759  }
2760  VectorCopy(spline->next->point.origin, points[i + 1]);
2761 
2762  while (count > 2)
2763  {
2764  for (i = 0; i < count - 1; i++)
2765  {
2766  VectorSubtract(points[i + 1], points[i], dist);
2767  VectorMA(points[i], tension, dist, points[i]);
2768  }
2769  count--;
2770  }
2771 
2772  VectorCopy(points[0], out1);
2773  VectorCopy(points[1], out2);

2782 qboolean BG_TraverseSpline(float *deltaTime, splinePath_t **pSpline)
2783 {
2784  float dist;
2785 
2786  while ((*deltaTime) > 1)
2787  {
2788  (*deltaTime) -= 1;
2789  dist = (*pSpline)->length * (*deltaTime);
2790 
2791  if (!(*pSpline)->next || (*pSpline)->next->length == 0.f)
2792  {
2793  return qfalse;
2794  //Com_Error( ERR_DROP, "Spline path end passed (%s)", (*pSpline)->point.name );
2795  }
2796 
2797  (*pSpline) = (*pSpline)->next;
2798  *deltaTime = dist / (*pSpline)->length;
2799  }
2800 
2801  while ((*deltaTime) < 0)
2802  {
2803  dist = -((*pSpline)->length * (*deltaTime));
2804 
2805  if (!(*pSpline)->prev || (*pSpline)->prev->length == 0.f)
2806  {
2807  return qfalse;
2808  //Com_Error( ERR_DROP, "Spline path end passed (%s)", (*pSpline)->point.name );
2809  }
2810 
2811  (*pSpline) = (*pSpline)->prev;
2812  (*deltaTime) = 1 - (dist / (*pSpline)->length);
2813  }
2814 
2815  return qtrue;

2827 qboolean BG_RaySphereIntersection(float radius, vec3_t origin, splineSegment_t *path, float *t0, float *t1)
2828 {
2829  vec3_t v;
2830  float b, c, d;
2831 
2832  VectorSubtract(path->start, origin, v);
2833 
2834  b = 2 * DotProduct(v, path->v_norm);
2835  c = DotProduct(v, v) - (radius * radius);
2836 
2837  d = (b * b) - (4 * c);
2838  if (d < 0)
2839  {
2840  return qfalse;
2841  }
2842  d = sqrt(d);
2843 
2844  *t0 = (-b + d) * 0.5f;
2845  *t1 = (-b - d) * 0.5f;
2846 
2847  return qtrue;
2848 }

3343  case TR_LINEAR:
3344  VectorCopy(tr->trDelta, result);
3345  break;
3346  case TR_SINE:
3347  deltaTime = (atTime - tr->trTime) / (float) tr->trDuration;
3348  phase = cos(deltaTime * M_TAU_F); // derivative of sin = cos
3349  phase *= M_TAU_F * 2 * 1000 / (float)tr->trDuration;
3350  VectorScale(tr->trDelta, phase, result);
3351  break;
3352  case TR_LINEAR_STOP:
3353  if (atTime > tr->trTime + tr->trDuration || atTime < tr->trTime)
3354  {
3355  VectorClear(result);
3356  return;
3357  }
3358  VectorCopy(tr->trDelta, result);
3359  break;
3360  case TR_GRAVITY:
3361  deltaTime = (atTime - tr->trTime) * 0.001f; // milliseconds to seconds
3362  VectorCopy(tr->trDelta, result);
3363  result[2] -= DEFAULT_GRAVITY * deltaTime; // FIXME: local gravity...
3364  break;
3365  case TR_GRAVITY_LOW:
3366  deltaTime = (atTime - tr->trTime) * 0.001f; // milliseconds to seconds
3367  VectorCopy(tr->trDelta, result);
3368  result[2] -= (DEFAULT_GRAVITY * 0.3f) * deltaTime; // FIXME: local gravity...
3369  break;
3370  case TR_GRAVITY_FLOAT:
3371  deltaTime = (atTime - tr->trTime) * 0.001f; // milliseconds to seconds
3372  VectorCopy(tr->trDelta, result);
3373  result[2] -= (DEFAULT_GRAVITY * 0.2f) * deltaTime;
3374  break;
3375  // acceleration
3376  case TR_ACCELERATE: // trDelta is eventual speed
3377  if (atTime > tr->trTime + tr->trDuration)
3378  {
3379  VectorClear(result);
3380  return;
3381  }
3382  deltaTime = (atTime - tr->trTime) * 0.001f; // milliseconds to seconds
3383  // phase = deltaTime / (float)tr->trDuration; // TODO: phase is never read
3384  VectorScale(tr->trDelta, deltaTime * deltaTime, result);
3385  break;
3386  case TR_DECCELERATE: // trDelta is breaking force
3387  if (atTime > tr->trTime + tr->trDuration)
3388  {
3389  VectorClear(result);
3390  return;
3391  }
3392  deltaTime = (atTime - tr->trTime) * 0.001f; // milliseconds to seconds
3393  VectorScale(tr->trDelta, deltaTime, result);
3394  break;
3395  case TR_SPLINE:
3396  case TR_LINEAR_PATH:
3397  VectorClear(result);
3398  break;
3399  // TODO : case not handle
3400  //case TR_LINEAR_STOP_BACK:
3401  //case TR_GRAVITY_PAUSED:
3402  default:
3403  Com_Error(ERR_DROP, "BG_EvaluateTrajectoryDelta: unknown trType: %i", tr->trTime);
3404  }
3405 }

3414 void BG_GetMarkDir(const vec3_t dir, const vec3_t normal, vec3_t out)
3415 {
3416  vec3_t ndir, lnormal;
3417  float minDot = 0.3f;
3418  int x = 0;
3419 
3420  if (dir[0] < 0.001f && dir[1] < 0.001f)
3421  {
3422  VectorCopy(dir, out);
3423  return;
3424  }
3425 
3426  if (VectorLengthSquared(normal) < Square(1.f)) // this is needed to get rid of (0,0,0) normals (happens with entities?)
3427  {
3428  VectorSet(lnormal, 0.f, 0.f, 1.f);
3429  }
3430  else
3431  {
3432  //VectorCopy( normal, lnormal );
3433  //VectorNormalizeFast( lnormal );
3434  VectorNormalize2(normal, lnormal);
3435  }
3436 
3437  VectorNegate(dir, ndir);
3438  VectorNormalize(ndir);
3439  if (normal[2] > .8f)
3440  {
3441  minDot = .7f;
3442  }
3443 
3444  // make sure it makrs the impact surface
3445  while (DotProduct(ndir, lnormal) < minDot && x < 10)
3446  {
3447  VectorMA(ndir, .5f, lnormal, ndir);
3448  VectorNormalize(ndir);
3449 
3450  x++;
3451  }
3452 
3453 #ifdef GAMEDLL
3454  if (x >= 10)
3455  {
3456  if (g_developer.integer)
3457  {
3458  Com_Printf("BG_GetMarkDir loops: %i\n", x);
3459  }
3460  }
3461 #endif // GAMEDLL
3462 
3463  VectorCopy(ndir, out);
3464 }
